HEADWORD: Oversupply
<hw>O`ver*sup*ply"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To supply in
excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oversupply</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Oversupply
<hw>O"ver*sup*ply`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An excessive supply; a
supply in excess of demand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A general <qex>oversupply</qex> or excess of all commodities.</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Mill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oversure</ent>⟦br⟧
